 "_meta": {
  "source": "aura_trigger_schema.json (corpus 319 aura2 triggers + BuffTrigger2.lua) - NOT a prototype scan; aura2 is function-driven. read-axis = the surface conditions pair on.",
  "provenance": "Fields + corpus_pct from 319 aura2 triggers in the OUR-WA corpus (plane/diagnose.py lens). Value-domains referenced to wa_index/value_domains.json (already sourced from WA's own Types.lua via extract.lua) where a shared table exists; else the inline domain is confirmed against WeakAuras/BuffTrigger2.lua on disk. Residue fields (subeventPrefix/Suffix, itemName/itemSlot, powertype, castType, genericShowOn, use_showgcd, form — cross-type leftovers) are deliberately EXCLUDED.",
  "why": "The single most-used reader in real authorship (66% of the corpus) but function-driven, so absent from index.json's prototype scan. This closes that gap. A WA reads native buff-window state and flattens it; this names the fields that do the reading. See memory/aura-trigger-schema-and-matching + wa-reads-and-flattens-native-state."
